gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Timberwolves 127, Grizzlies 103
gameRecap.excerpt: The Timberwolves defeated the Grizzlies, 127-103 to win their sixth consecutive game and improve to 17-4 on the year. Karl-Anthony Towns led Minnesota with 24 points, seven rebounds, and five assists as Rudy Gobert added 16 points, 20 rebounds, and six blocks. This was Goberts second consecutive game with 20 rebounds and the third of the year. Jaren Jackson led the Grizzlies with 21 points as Desmond Bane added 16 points. The Grizzlies move to 6-15.
